{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"I am passionate about the American landscape"},{"time":4000,"text":"and how the physical form of the land,"},{"time":6000,"text":"from the great Central Valley of California"},{"time":8000,"text":"to the bedrock of Manhattan,"},{"time":10000,"text":"has really shaped our history and our character."},{"time":13000,"text":"But one thing is clear."},{"time":15000,"text":"In the last 100 years alone,"},{"time":17000,"text":"our country -- and this is a sprawl map of America --"},{"time":20000,"text":"our country has systematically"},{"time":23000,"text":"flattened and homogenized the landscape"},{"time":25000,"text":"to the point where we've forgotten"},{"time":27000,"text":"our relationship with the plants and animals"},{"time":29000,"text":"that live alongside us"},{"time":31000,"text":"and the dirt beneath our feet."},{"time":33000,"text":"And so, how I see my work contributing"},{"time":35000,"text":"is sort of trying to literally re-imagine these connections"},{"time":38000,"text":"and physically rebuild them."},{"time":40000,"text":"This graph represents what we're dealing with now"},{"time":43000,"text":"in the built environment."},{"time":45000,"text":"And it's really a conflux"},{"time":47000,"text":"of urban population rising,"},{"time":49000,"text":"biodiversity plummeting"},{"time":51000,"text":"and also, of course, sea levels rising"},{"time":54000,"text":"and climate changing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":56000,"text":"So when I also think about design,"},{"time":58000,"text":"I think about"},{"time":60000,"text":"trying to rework and re-engage"},{"time":62000,"text":"the lines on this graph"},{"time":65000,"text":"in a more productive way."},{"time":67000,"text":"And you can see from the arrow here"},{"time":69000,"text":"indicating \"you are here,\""},{"time":71000,"text":"I'm trying to sort of blend and meld"},{"time":73000,"text":"these two very divergent fields"},{"time":75000,"text":"of urbanism and ecology,"},{"time":77000,"text":"and sort of bring them together in an exciting new way."},{"time":81000,"text":"So the era of big infrastructure is over."},{"time":85000,"text":"I mean, these sort of top-down,"},{"time":87000,"text":"mono-functional, capital-intensive solutions"},{"time":89000,"text":"are really not going to cut it."},{"time":91000,"text":"We need new tools and new approaches."},{"time":94000,"text":"Similarly, the idea of architecture"},{"time":96000,"text":"as this sort of object in the field,"},{"time":98000,"text":"devoid of context,"},{"time":100000,"text":"is really not the --"},{"time":102000,"text":"excuse me, it's fairly blatant --"},{"time":104000,"text":"is really not the approach"},{"time":107000,"text":"that we need to take."},{"time":109000,"text":"So we need new stories,"},{"time":111000,"text":"new heroes and new tools."}]},{"cues":[{"time":114000,"text":"So now I want to introduce you to my new hero"},{"time":117000,"text":"in the global climate change war,"},{"time":119000,"text":"and that is the eastern oyster."},{"time":121000,"text":"So, albeit a very small creature"},{"time":123000,"text":"and very modest,"},{"time":125000,"text":"this creature is incredible,"},{"time":127000,"text":"because it can agglomerate"},{"time":129000,"text":"into these mega-reef structures."},{"time":131000,"text":"It can grow; you can grow it;"},{"time":133000,"text":"and -- did I mention? -- it's quite tasty."},{"time":136000,"text":"So the oyster was the basis"},{"time":138000,"text":"for a manifesto-like urban design project"},{"time":141000,"text":"that I did about the New York Harbor"},{"time":143000,"text":"called \"oyster-tecture.\""},{"time":145000,"text":"And the core idea of oyster-tecture is to harness the biological power"},{"time":148000,"text":"of mussels, eelgrass and oysters --"},{"time":151000,"text":"species that live in the harbor --"},{"time":153000,"text":"and, at the same time,"},{"time":155000,"text":"harness the power of people"},{"time":157000,"text":"who live in the community"},{"time":159000,"text":"towards making change now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162000,"text":"Here's a map of my city, New York City,"},{"time":165000,"text":"showing inundation in red."},{"time":167000,"text":"And what's circled is the site that I'm going to talk about,"},{"time":169000,"text":"the Gowanus Canal and Governors Island."},{"time":172000,"text":"If you look here at this map,"},{"time":174000,"text":"showing everything in blue"},{"time":176000,"text":"is out in the water,"},{"time":178000,"text":"and everything in yellow is upland."},{"time":180000,"text":"But you can see, even just intuit, from this map,"},{"time":183000,"text":"that the harbor has dredged and flattened,"},{"time":186000,"text":"and went from a rich, three-dimensional mosaic to flat muck"},{"time":189000,"text":"in really a matter of years."},{"time":192000,"text":"Another set of views of actually the Gowanus Canal itself."},{"time":195000,"text":"Now the Gowanus is particularly smelly -- I will admit it."},{"time":198000,"text":"There are problems of sewage overflow"},{"time":200000,"text":"and contamination,"},{"time":202000,"text":"but I would also argue that almost every city"},{"time":205000,"text":"has this exact condition,"},{"time":207000,"text":"and it's a condition that we're all facing."},{"time":209000,"text":"And here's a map of that condition,"},{"time":211000,"text":"showing the contaminants in yellow and green,"},{"time":214000,"text":"exacerbated by this new flow of"},{"time":216000,"text":"storm-surge and sea-level rise."},{"time":218000,"text":"So we really had a lot to deal with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"When we started this project,"},{"time":222000,"text":"one of the core ideas was to look back in history"},{"time":225000,"text":"and try to understand what was there."},{"time":227000,"text":"And you can see from this map,"},{"time":229000,"text":"there's this incredible geographical signature"},{"time":231000,"text":"of a series of islands"},{"time":233000,"text":"that were out in the harbor"},{"time":235000,"text":"and a matrix of salt marshes and beaches"},{"time":238000,"text":"that served as natural wave attenuation"},{"time":240000,"text":"for the upland settlement."},{"time":242000,"text":"We also learned at this time"},{"time":244000,"text":"that you could eat an oyster about the size of a dinner plate"},{"time":247000,"text":"in the Gowanus Canal itself."},{"time":250000,"text":"So our concept is really this back-to-the-future concept,"},{"time":253000,"text":"harnessing the intelligence of that land settlement pattern."},{"time":256000,"text":"And the idea has two core stages."},{"time":258000,"text":"One is to develop a new artificial ecology,"},{"time":261000,"text":"a reef out in the harbor,"},{"time":263000,"text":"that would then protect new settlement patterns"},{"time":265000,"text":"inland and the Gowanus."},{"time":267000,"text":"Because if you have cleaner water and slower water,"},{"time":269000,"text":"you can imagine a new way of living with that water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"So the project really addresses these three core issues"},{"time":275000,"text":"in a new and exciting way, I think."},{"time":278000,"text":"Here we are, back to our hero, the oyster."},{"time":281000,"text":"And again, it's this incredibly exciting animal."},{"time":284000,"text":"It accepts algae and detritus in one end,"},{"time":286000,"text":"and through this beautiful, glamorous"},{"time":288000,"text":"set of stomach organs,"},{"time":290000,"text":"out the other end comes cleaner water."},{"time":293000,"text":"And one oyster can filter up to 50 gallons of water a day."},{"time":296000,"text":"Oyster reefs also covered"},{"time":298000,"text":"about a quarter of our harbor"},{"time":300000,"text":"and were capable of filtering water in the harbor in a matter of days."},{"time":303000,"text":"They were key in our culture and our economy."},{"time":307000,"text":"Basically, New York was built"},{"time":309000,"text":"on the backs of oystermen,"},{"time":311000,"text":"and our streets were literally built over oyster shells."},{"time":314000,"text":"This image"},{"time":316000,"text":"is an image of an oyster cart,"},{"time":318000,"text":"which is now as ubiquitous as the hotdog cart is today."},{"time":321000,"text":"So again, we got the short end of the deal there."},{"time":323000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":325000,"text":"Finally, oysters can attenuate"},{"time":327000,"text":"and agglomerate onto each other"},{"time":329000,"text":"and form these amazing natural reef structures."},{"time":332000,"text":"They really become nature's wave attenuators."},{"time":335000,"text":"And they become the bedrock"},{"time":337000,"text":"of any harbor ecosystem."},{"time":339000,"text":"Many, many species depend on them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":341000,"text":"So we were inspired by the oyster,"},{"time":343000,"text":"but I was also inspired by the life cycle of the oyster."},{"time":346000,"text":"It can move from a fertilized egg"},{"time":349000,"text":"to a spat, which is when they're floating through the water,"},{"time":352000,"text":"and when they're ready to attach onto another oyster,"},{"time":355000,"text":"to an adult male oyster or female oyster,"},{"time":357000,"text":"in a number of weeks."},{"time":360000,"text":"We reinterpreted this life cycle"},{"time":362000,"text":"on the scale of our sight"},{"time":364000,"text":"and took the Gowanus"},{"time":366000,"text":"as a giant oyster nursery"},{"time":368000,"text":"where oysters would be grown up in the Gowanus,"},{"time":370000,"text":"then paraded down in their spat stage"},{"time":372000,"text":"and seeded out on the Bayridge Reef."},{"time":375000,"text":"And so the core idea here"},{"time":377000,"text":"was to hit the reset button"},{"time":379000,"text":"and regenerate an ecology over time"},{"time":381000,"text":"that was regenerative and cleaning"},{"time":383000,"text":"and productive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":385000,"text":"How does the reef work? Well, it's very, very simple."},{"time":388000,"text":"A core concept here"},{"time":390000,"text":"is that climate change"},{"time":392000,"text":"isn't something that --"},{"time":394000,"text":"the answers won't land down from the Moon."},{"time":397000,"text":"And with a $20 billion price tag,"},{"time":399000,"text":"we should simply start and get to work with what we have now"},{"time":401000,"text":"and what's in front of us."},{"time":403000,"text":"So this image is simply showing --"},{"time":405000,"text":"it's a field of marine piles"},{"time":407000,"text":"interconnected with this woven fuzzy rope."},{"time":410000,"text":"What is fuzzy rope, you ask?"},{"time":413000,"text":"It's just that; it's this very inexpensive thing,"},{"time":416000,"text":"available practically at your hardware store, and it's very cheap."},{"time":419000,"text":"So we imagine that we would actually"},{"time":421000,"text":"potentially even host a bake sale"},{"time":423000,"text":"to start our new project."},{"time":425000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":427000,"text":"So in the studio, rather than drawing,"},{"time":429000,"text":"we began to learn how to knit."},{"time":431000,"text":"The concept was to really knit this rope together"},{"time":434000,"text":"and develop this new soft infrastructure"},{"time":436000,"text":"for the oysters to grow on."},{"time":438000,"text":"You can see in the diagram how it grows over time"},{"time":441000,"text":"from an infrastructural space"},{"time":443000,"text":"into a new public urban space."},{"time":446000,"text":"And that grows over time dynamically"},{"time":449000,"text":"with the threat of climate change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":451000,"text":"It also creates this incredibly interesting, I think,"},{"time":454000,"text":"new amphibious public space,"},{"time":457000,"text":"where you can imagine working,"},{"time":459000,"text":"you can imagine recreating in a new way."},{"time":462000,"text":"In the end, what we realized we were making"},{"time":464000,"text":"was a new blue-green watery park"},{"time":467000,"text":"for the next watery century --"},{"time":469000,"text":"an amphibious park, if you will."},{"time":471000,"text":"So get your Tevas on."},{"time":473000,"text":"So you can imagine scuba diving here."},{"time":475000,"text":"This is an image of high school students,"},{"time":477000,"text":"scuba divers that we worked with on our team."},{"time":479000,"text":"So you can imagine a sort of new manner of living"},{"time":482000,"text":"with a new relationship with the water,"},{"time":484000,"text":"and also a hybridizing of recreational and science programs"},{"time":487000,"text":"in terms of monitoring."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489000,"text":"Another new vocabulary word for the brave new world:"},{"time":492000,"text":"this is the word \"flupsy\" --"},{"time":494000,"text":"it's short for \"floating upwelling system.\""},{"time":497000,"text":"And this glorious, readily available device"},{"time":500000,"text":"is basically a floating raft"},{"time":502000,"text":"with an oyster nursery below."},{"time":504000,"text":"So the water is churned through this raft."},{"time":507000,"text":"You can see the eight chambers on the side"},{"time":509000,"text":"host little baby oysters and essentially force-feed them."},{"time":512000,"text":"So rather than having 10 oysters,"},{"time":515000,"text":"you have 10,000 oysters."},{"time":517000,"text":"And then those spat are then seeded."},{"time":519000,"text":"Here's the Gowanus future"},{"time":521000,"text":"with the oyster rafts on the shorelines --"},{"time":523000,"text":"the flupsification of the Gowanus."},{"time":526000,"text":"New word."},{"time":528000,"text":"And also showing oyster gardening for the community"},{"time":531000,"text":"along its edges."},{"time":533000,"text":"And finally, how much fun it would be"},{"time":535000,"text":"to watch the flupsy parade"},{"time":537000,"text":"and cheer on the oyster spats"},{"time":539000,"text":"as they go down to the reef."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"I get asked two questions about this project."},{"time":544000,"text":"One is: why isn't it happening now?"},{"time":546000,"text":"And the second one is: when can we eat the oysters?"},{"time":549000,"text":"And the answer is: not yet, they're working."},{"time":552000,"text":"But we imagine, with our calculations,"},{"time":554000,"text":"that by 2050,"},{"time":556000,"text":"you might be able to sink your teeth into a Gowanus oyster."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559000,"text":"To conclude, this is just one cross-section"},{"time":561000,"text":"of one piece of city,"},{"time":563000,"text":"but my dream is, my hope is,"},{"time":565000,"text":"that when you all go back to your own cities"},{"time":567000,"text":"that we can start to work together and collaborate"},{"time":570000,"text":"on remaking and reforming"},{"time":572000,"text":"a new urban landscape"},{"time":574000,"text":"towards a more sustainable, a more livable"},{"time":577000,"text":"and a more delicious future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}